ign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The young and the Ragefire</span><hr size=1> /em begins to twitch as she remembers the 5 rage camps she has helped on.<br>
<br>
Yup, 5 soap opera, edge of your seat, is KS guild_01 gonna try to gank the spawn after we sat here for three days.<br>
<br>
This change IS an improvement, but the Dev team needs to start thinking outside the box for this.  The encounter is your standard dragon bash - ho hum.  They have instituted some interesting quest/test things - like Ring of Fire in Acrylia.  Why not make a combat test where the guild HAS to keep the cleric alive through a cascading spawn cycle ending in Ragefire himself breathing fire and fury.  Let the trigger spawn once every 7 days - like Naggy, and on server up.  And let the encounter take a few hours - make it into a challenge again.  This would negate any KS issues (as long as the guild in question keeps the spawn cycle going, they own the spawn, and let the pearl be something that is returned to the cleric after triggering the cycle - just like the bard and druid epic trigger peices are.  This also prevents a flood of epics on to a server.  ONE encounter ONCE each week.  A guild HAS to have a cleric ready to trigger the spawn.  Sure let there be decent loot ready for rewarding folks, but let the encounter be a freaking blast to attend and loot will be low on everyone's priority list.<br>
<br>
Least those are just my thoughts on the matter.<br>
<br>
G 0 d Bless,<br>
